abstract: Securing approval from Congress for the deal between the United States and 11 Pacific Rim nations could be the toughest fight President Obama faces in his final year in office.
snippet: Securing approval from Congress for the deal between the United States and 11 Pacific Rim nations could be the toughest fight President Obama faces in his final year in office.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — The United States, Japan and 10 other Pacific Rim nations on Monday reached final agreement on the largest regional trade accord in history, teeing up what could be the toughest fight President Obama will face in his final year in office: securing approval from Congress.

headline.main: Trans-Pacific Partnership Is Reached, but Faces Scrutiny in Congress
headline.print_headline: 11 Pacific Nations and U.S. Endorse Giant Trade Pact
